column12: Measurement condition : Ice; Clear , No Precipitation , Very Light Wind Swirling/Variable
column13: Ice and debris D/S of gauge. No more anchor ice in MMT part of channel but most of the channel D/S is still downstream PIC. Fully open by orifice line on right bank, still mostly ice on left bank under bridge by orifice line.
column14: @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ MMT was taken 5m D/S of the bridge and gauge. No anchor ice was left in MMT section whilst there was PIC both U/S and D/S. The channel was about 2m across with majority of the flow in the middle of the channel. Both edges had poor flow, so MMT required some tighter spacing in the middle of the channel. Spacing needed to be tighter than the usual 0.1m in one part of the channel (one panel was 0.05m spacing). Rocky bed with neither debris nor ice. PIC both U/S and D/S of orifice line and MMT section. Ice melting due to clear sunny skies and warm temperature. DWL taken on arrival. Stage had been steady prior to reset but needed 0.07m reset; after reset logger remained steady with no more resets required. Rail tie appears to have been flipped on its side, probably due to ice movement. Second DWL was more accurate as the first DWL was too far away from the sensor. The second DWL was taken right beside the sensor and rail tie providing a much more accurate reading. Slope of a smaller creek has more of an impact on stage, need to take DWLs as close to sensor as possible. Mid-section

column12: Measurement condition : Altered; Mostly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Light Wind Blowing Cross Stream
column13: Ice frozen to bottom, over ice flow.
column14: FT2 boot wade over ice.  All flow constricted to right bank. Upstream right bank has 100% of over ice flow, which flows overtop of the ice underneath the bridge. Appears that some flow is going under ice as well. Drilled through ice downstream of gauge after measurement. Measurement taken just downstream of gauge, over ice. Better measurement section than at right bank, upstream. Used FT2 under ice to estimate any under ice flow to add to the over ice flow. After drilling holes observed water and debris from over ice flow filling in to holes. Under ice measurement used minimum spacing in a narrow section, and had more errors that the above ice measurement. Imported the first over ice measurement (M1) and added the discharge from the second under ice measurement (M2) to the total discharge on the front sheet. Both measurements had angled flow and SNR errors.  First DWL taken from over ice flow. OTT is under clear ice, can see sensor. Drilled hole in channel after measurement, roughly 0.300m water under ice. Reset applied in logger from first DWL at 14:40, assumed that OTT is connected to over ice flow due to smalled reset. Logger crashed at 14:45, did not come back online until 14:50. Following measurement, drilled hole causing water level to change due to water over ice filling in to hole, observed in logger at 15:20. Water level recovered to normal shortly after. Took second DWL from hole though ice, found similar DWL to before. No reset at second DWL. Mid-section
